Justin Bieber’s New Song Is All About S-E-X | Vanity FairVanity FairSign InAdult ContemporaryJustin Bieber’s New Song Is All About S-E-X“Oh Girl” has Bieber praising his lady friend’s body.by Richard LawsonFebruary 22, 2016 2:38 pmEmailFacebookTwitterBy Daniel Torok/PatrickMcMullan.com.Justin Bieber, onetime and aspiring future monkey owner, has had a new song leak, continuing his recent streak of cool, laid-back R&B grooves. The track is called “Oh Girl,” and it is about the ancient and sacred act of doing it.Well, O.K., it’s mostly about really liking a girl, and there are no fully explicit references to intercourse. But it’s pretty plain that the barely subtextual subject of the song is, in fact, the having of sex. Bumping. Smooshing. Knocking the proverbial boots. Humping, if you want to be crass about it. Boffing. Screwing. Taking the light rail to Pound Town. Making the beast with two backs. The Irish nine-monther. Rutting. The honeymoon hug. The bishop’s visit. Friday-night specialing. Straight-up fucking. Whatever you want to call it, really, that’s what Justin Bieber’s song is about.With lyrics like “Your body is so insane / Making me call your name” and “It’s like a rush / Every single time we touch,” Bieber is clearly singing to a young lady about their intimate moments. But in a romantic way, of course. This isn’t some filthy paean to doing the nasty. It’s a soulful rumination on the specialness of Justin’s connection with one particular girl. Whether you would like to pretend you are that girl as you listen to the song, closing your eyes and making a sad little whimpering, gurgling sort of sound with your mouth while you sway back and forth? Well, that’s entirely up to you.Full ScreenPhotos:1/7We’re a BelieberDiscovered when he was 14, 16-year-old Bieber has accomplished remarkable feats all within the past two years: a platinum debut album (My World), two Grammy nominations, four American Music Awards (he beat out Eminem and Lady Gaga for artist of the year), and a feature film, Never Say Never, out February 11. Did we mention a world tour?
Bieber wears a shirt by Gucci. Grooming products by Bumble and Bumble and Make Up For Ever. See complete credits.“Check out my six-pack!” Bieber said (and we’re not talking about Coca-Cola!). The September 2009 Vanity Fair collectors’ issue, featuring Michael Jackson with a similarly exposed chest, happened to be found on set and prompted Justin’s desire to emulate his moonwalking idol. “I want to be like Michael!” he exclaimed. Lisa Robinson’s interview with a teenage Michael Jackson in this same issue excited the Biebs; the legendary music writer was soon to interview our present-day teenage sensation, leaving Michael and Justin with much more in common than just an open shirt.
Bieber wears a shirt by Band of Outsiders. See complete credits.Every move he makes, the world watches. Screaming fans and flashing lights don’t phase the Biebs, as he poses with his other source of inspiration: every Elvis record imaginable. It didn’t take much to get the extras in the shoot excited about Justin. Not knowing that he would be there, the girls shrieked deafeningly when they walked onto the set. We overheard one adorable extra say, “I went to the bathroom so many times just so I could get a glimpse of where Justin was. I never even really had to go!”
Bieber wears a turtleneck and jeans by Thom Browne New York; shoes by Keds. See complete credits.Truly a modern-day Renaissance man, Justin attracts as many fans on the croquet court as he does on the stage. We hope a change of career is not in the near future, though one in croquet appears promising.
